-- GE vice chairman Wright to retire
-- 
-- Fri Feb 1, 2008 11:03am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/02/01/us-ge-wright-idUSWNAS901220080201

 

 BOSTON  (Reuters) - General Electric Co ( GE.N ) said on Friday that vice chairman Bob Wright, former head of the company's NBC arm, will retire on May 1. 

 The disclosure came in a filing with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission. Wright had served as chief executive of NBC before handing the reins to Jeff Zucker in February 2007. (Reporting by  Scott Malone , editing by Gerald E. McCormick)